'''Mao Xiaobing''' ({{zh|c=毛小兵|p=Máo Xiǎobīng}}; born April 1965) is a former Chinese politician and mining executive. He was the [[Party Committee Secretary|Communist Party Secretary]] of [[Xining]], capital of [[Qinghai]] province, and former chief executive of [[Western Mining Company]], a diversified natural resources company with a large portfolio projects in China's western interior. Mao was investigated for corruption by the Communist Party's [[CCFDI|top anti-graft body]] in April 2014, and was expelled from the party three months later for abuse of power and other offenses.

==Biography==
Mao was born and raised in [[Changde]], [[Hunan]], he received his [[Bachelor of Engineering]] degree from [[University of Science and Technology Beijing]], in July 1985, majoring in Industrial automation at the Department of Automation.<ref name="fish">{{cite web |url=http://news.qq.com/a/20140425/000854.htm |script-title=zh:西宁市委书记毛小兵被查 曾拿154万元税前薪酬|date=25 April 2014|publisher= |work=Tencent |language=zh }}</ref><ref name="duck">{{cite web |url=http://news.163.com/14/0424/22/9QKO7AVF00014JB5.html |script-title=zh:青海省委常委西宁市委书记毛小兵被调查 |date=24 April 2014 |publisher= |work=163.COM |language=zh }}</ref><ref name="lion">{{cite web |url=http://news.ifeng.com/a/20140424/40029713_0.shtml |script-title=zh:青海省委常委、西宁市委书记毛小兵被查(图) |date=24 April 2014|publisher= |work=Ifeng |language=zh }}</ref>

Mao joined the [[Communist Party of China]] in December 1984 and became involved in politics in July 1985.<ref name="fish" /><ref name="duck" /><ref name="lion" />

From July 1985 to April 2000, Mao worked in the China Nonferrous Metals Industry Corporation, a state-owned company under the jurisdiction of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China]].<ref name="fish" /> From April 2000 to April 2009, Mao worked as the chief executive of [[Western Mining Company]], a large state-owned natural resources company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:WHZnAj-YJkoJ:investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=30325816&ticker=601168:CH&previousCapId=22915103&previousTitle=WESTERN%2520MINING%2520CO%2520-A+Mao+Xiaobing&cd=6&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=hk&client=firefox-a|title=Background: Mr. Xiaobing Mao serves as the Executive Chairman of Western Mining Co. Group, Ltd. |date= |publisher= |work= }}</ref> At the same times, Mao studied at [[Central Party School of the Communist Party of China]], he also earned a [[doctor of engineering]] from [[Central South University]].<ref name="fish" /><ref name="duck" /><ref name="lion" />

In April 2009 he was promoted to become the acting mayor and CPC Party vice-secretary of [[Xi'ning]], a position he held until December 2011.<ref name="fish" /> In December 2011, Mao was elevated to the CPC Party Secretary of [[Xi'ning]], capital city of [[Qinghai|Qinghai province]],<ref name="tiger">{{cite web |url=http://www.china.org.cn/china/2014-04/24/content_32202922.htm |title=Official probed for suspected serious violations |date=24 April 2014 |publisher=China |work= }}</ref> he was appointed to the [[Politics of Qinghai|Party Standing Committee of Qinghai province]] in May 2012.<ref name="fish" /><ref name="bee">{{cite web |url=http://www.ecns.cn/2014/04-25/111145.shtml |title=Qinghai official probed for suspected serious violations |date=25 April 2014 |publisher= |work=Chinanews }}</ref>

On April 24, 2014, Mao was being investigated by the [[Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Communist Party of China]] for "serious violations of laws and regulations". Mao was subject to many formal complaints filed online for alleged abuses during his term in office and his time at the helm of Western Mining Company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.js.xinhuanet.com/2014-04/25/c_1110403192.htm |script-title=zh:西宁市委书记毛小兵被查 曾多次遭网贴举报 |date=25 April 2014|publisher= |work=Xinhuanet |language=zh }}</ref> The party investigation, concluded on July 16, concluded that Mao "abused his power for the illicit gain of others, solicited and accepted huge bribes" and "committed adultery."<ref name=axin>{{cite news|script-title=zh:青海省委原常委毛小兵被开除党籍和公职|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/politics/2014-07/16/c_1111638107.htm|work=Xinhua|date=July 16, 2014}}</ref> Mao was expelled from the Communist Party of China; his criminal case was moved to prosecution agencies for processing.<ref name=axin/> He was sentenced for life in prison on May 11, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url =http://news.qq.com/a/20170511/035781.htm|script-title=zh:西宁市委原书记毛小兵受贿1.04亿被判无期|accessdate = May 11, 2017|work=qq.com}}</ref>

Mao was a member of the 10th National Committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]], and a member of the 11th [[National People's Congress]]. Mao is also the former Vice-President of [[China Chamber of International Commerce]] (CCOIC), the Managing Director of China Association of Young Entrepreneurs and [[China Non-Ferrous Metals Industry Association]], he was a member of [[All-China Youth Federation]]. Prior to his investigation, Mao was also a part-time professor at the [[China University of Geosciences (Beijing)|China University of Geosciences]] and [[University of Science and Technology Beijing]], he also a guest professor at the [[Guizhou University]].

Mao Xiaobing is from [[Mao Zedong]]'s home province of Hunan, but is not related to the Chairman.

